<ol start=3D"7">
<li>
<p>Introduction to expert system.</p></li>
</ol>
<p>Here=E2=80=99s a <strong>structured overview</strong> of <strong>Expert =
Systems in AI</strong>:</p>
<hr>
<h2 id=3D"ArtificialIntelligence-1=EF=B8=8F=E2=83=A3Definition.3"><strong>1=
=EF=B8=8F=E2=83=A3 Definition</strong></h2>
<p>An <strong>Expert System (ES)</strong> is a <strong>computer program tha=
t mimics the decision-making ability of a human expert</strong>.</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>Uses <strong>knowledge and reasoning</strong> to solve problems in a spe=
cific domain.</p></li>
<li>
<p>Provides <strong>advice, diagnosis, or recommendations</strong>.</p></li=
>
<li>
<p>One of the earliest practical applications of AI.</p></li>
</ul>
<hr>
<h2 id=3D"ArtificialIntelligence-2=EF=B8=8F=E2=83=A3ComponentsofanExpertSys=
tem"><strong>2=EF=B8=8F=E2=83=A3 Components of an Expert System</strong></h=
2>
<div class=3D"table-wrap">
<table data-table-width=3D"760" data-layout=3D"default" data-local-id=3D"47=
912b6a-50cf-43a5-a0e2-53ddeb85fe90" class=3D"confluenceTable">
<tbody>
<tr>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p>Component</p></th>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p>Function</p></th>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><strong>Knowledge Base</strong></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Stores facts and rules about the domain (e.g., =E2=80=9CIf fever and cou=
gh, then possible flu=E2=80=9D)</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><strong>Inference Engine</strong></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Applies reasoning to the knowledge base to deduce new facts or solve pro=
blems</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><strong>Working Memory</strong></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Stores temporary facts about the current problem or session</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><strong>User Interface</strong></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Allows user to interact with the system (input queries, receive advice)<=
/p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><strong>Explanation Facility</strong></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Explains reasoning steps to the user (=E2=80=9CBecause symptom X and Y, =
the diagnosis is Z=E2=80=9D)</p></td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div>
<hr>
<h2 id=3D"ArtificialIntelligence-3=EF=B8=8F=E2=83=A3CharacteristicsofExpert=
Systems"><strong>3=EF=B8=8F=E2=83=A3 Characteristics of Expert Systems</str=
ong></h2>
<ul>
<li>
<p><strong>Domain-specific:</strong> Expert in a narrow field (medical diag=
nosis, engineering, troubleshooting)</p></li>
<li>
<p><strong>Rule-based reasoning:</strong> Often uses <strong>IF-THEN rules<=
/strong></p></li>
<li>
<p><strong>Handles uncertainty:</strong> Uses probabilistic or fuzzy logic =
reasoning</p></li>
<li>
<p><strong>Non-learning (usually):</strong> Knowledge is manually input by =
experts (some modern systems integrate learning)</p></li>
</ul>
<hr>
<h2 id=3D"ArtificialIntelligence-4=EF=B8=8F=E2=83=A3TypesofExpertSystems"><=
strong>4=EF=B8=8F=E2=83=A3 Types of Expert Systems</strong></h2>
<ol start=3D"1">
<li>
<p><strong>Rule-Based Systems:</strong> Use IF-THEN rules for reasoning</p>=
</li>
<li>
<p><strong>Frame-Based Systems:</strong> Organize knowledge in structures (=
frames) with slots and values</p></li>
<li>
<p><strong>Fuzzy Expert Systems:</strong> Handle uncertainty with fuzzy log=
ic</p></li>
<li>
<p><strong>Case-Based Reasoning Systems:</strong> Solve new problems based =
on <strong>similar past cases</strong></p></li>
</ol>
<hr>
<h2 id=3D"ArtificialIntelligence-5=EF=B8=8F=E2=83=A3ApplicationsofExpertSys=
tems"><strong>5=EF=B8=8F=E2=83=A3 Applications of Expert Systems</strong></=
h2>
<ul>
<li>
<p><strong>Medical Diagnosis:</strong> MYCIN, CADUCEUS</p></li>
<li>
<p><strong>Engineering &amp; Troubleshooting:</strong> Fault detection in m=
achines or circuits</p></li>
<li>
<p><strong>Financial Systems:</strong> Loan approval, stock market analysis=
</p></li>
<li>
<p><strong>Process Control:</strong> Chemical plant or nuclear plant monito=
ring</p></li>
<li>
<p><strong>Customer Support &amp; Help Desk Automation</strong></p></li>
</ul>
<hr>
<h2 id=3D"ArtificialIntelligence-6=EF=B8=8F=E2=83=A3Advantages"><strong>6=
=EF=B8=8F=E2=83=A3 Advantages</strong></h2>
<ul>
<li>
<p>Consistent decision-making</p></li>
<li>
<p>Can provide <strong>expert-level advice</strong> in absence of a human e=
xpert</p></li>
<li>
<p>Can store and manage <strong>large volumes of knowledge</strong></p></li=
>
<li>
<p>Explains reasoning to users</p></li>
</ul>
<hr>
<h2 id=3D"ArtificialIntelligence-7=EF=B8=8F=E2=83=A3Limitations"><strong>7=
=EF=B8=8F=E2=83=A3 Limitations</strong></h2>
<ul>
<li>
<p>Knowledge acquisition is <strong>time-consuming and difficult</strong></=
p></li>
<li>
<p>Limited to <strong>specific domains</strong></p></li>
<li>
<p>Cannot handle problems outside its knowledge base</p></li>
<li>
<p>Usually lacks <strong>common-sense reasoning</strong></p></li>
</ul>
<hr>
<h3 id=3D"ArtificialIntelligence-=E2=9C=85Summary.6">=E2=9C=85 <strong>Summ=
ary</strong></h3>
<ul>
<li>
<p>An <strong>Expert System</strong> is a <strong>knowledge-based AI system=
</strong> that simulates human expertise.</p></li>
<li>
<p><strong>Components:</strong> Knowledge base, inference engine, working m=
emory, user interface, explanation facility</p></li>
<li>
<p><strong>Uses:</strong> Medical, engineering, finance, process control</p=
></li>
<li>
<p><strong>Strengths:</strong> Expert advice, consistency, explainability</=
p></li>
<li>
<p><strong>Weaknesses:</strong> Domain-specific, knowledge acquisition, lim=
ited reasoning</p></li>
</ul>
<hr>
<p>I can create a <strong>diagram showing the structure of an expert system=
, including the knowledge base, inference engine, and user interface</stron=
