<p>Here=E2=80=99s a <strong>concise yet informative overview</strong> of <s=
trong>Learning Algorithms in Machine Learning</strong> focusing on <strong>=
Supervised and Unsupervised (Clustering) methods</strong>:</p>
<hr>
<h2 id=3D"ArtificialIntelligence-1=EF=B8=8F=E2=83=A3LearningAlgorithmsOverv=
iew"><strong>1=EF=B8=8F=E2=83=A3 Learning Algorithms Overview</strong></h2>
<p><strong>Learning algorithms</strong> are <strong>procedures or methods u=
sed to train a model</strong> from data.</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p><strong>Input:</strong> Data (labeled or unlabeled)</p></li>
<li>
<p><strong>Output:</strong> Model that can make predictions or identify pat=
terns</p></li>
<li>
<p>Categories: <strong>Supervised Learning</strong> and <strong>Unsupervise=
d Learning</strong> (Clustering)</p></li>
</ul>
<hr>
<h2 id=3D"ArtificialIntelligence-2=EF=B8=8F=E2=83=A3SupervisedLearning"><st=
rong>2=EF=B8=8F=E2=83=A3 Supervised Learning</strong></h2>
<p><strong>Definition:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>Learns a function from <strong>labeled data</strong> (input-output pairs=
).</p></li>
<li>
<p>Goal: Predict the <strong>output (label)</strong> for new unseen inputs.=
</p></li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Workflow:</strong></p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
